events.body: Given that this proposal is in Draft status and hasn't evolved for the last three years, shouldn't it be marked Rejected?
I don't really have an opinion on that, I would just like to fix that typo:-)

> Given that this proposal is in Draft status and hasn't evolved for the last three years, shouldn't it be marked Rejected?

Similar to other proposals, BIP-49 is in production, albeit with modified version bytes (c.f. #762 ). Electrum and Trezor are probably the two largest wallets that implement this spec.
If @DanielWeigl is MIA, would someone like to take over this BIP?

> If @DanielWeigl is MIA, would someone like to take over this BIP?

I can take it if needed to push things forward.
Ive also made a PR to set it to `active` here https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/pull/809
